40625013@unknown@formal@none@1@S@If we examine the three types of change from the point of view of their internal structure we find an additional profound difference between the third and the first two, one that accounts for the notable difference between the responses they evoke.@@@@1@42@@oe@1-12-2014
40625014@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The first two types of change occur within the inward and immanent structure of the society.@@@@1@16@@oe@1-12-2014
