40625030@unknown@formal@none@1@S@At that point men become aware of the mystery of history called variously "fate", or "destiny", or "providence", and feel themselves caught helplessly in the writhing of a disrupted society.@@@@1@30@@oe@1-12-2014
40625031@unknown@formal@none@1@S@The reasons for this experience are rooted in the metaphysical characteristics of such a change.@@@@1@15@@oe@1-12-2014
40625032@unknown@formal@none@1@S@Of all forms of being, society, or community, has the greatest element of determinability.@@@@1@14@@oe@1-12-2014
